# Project 5 - Assign RBAC Roles in Microsoft Defender for Endpoint

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to assign Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) roles to users within Microsoft Defender for Endpoint.

RBAC ensures that users receive only the permissions required for their job responsibilities.

---

## Objective

- Learn RBAC
- Assign security roles
- Control user permissions
- Improve security administration

---

## Environment

| Item | Details |
|------|---------|
| Platform | Microsoft Defender for Endpoint |
| Operating System | Windows 11 |
| License | Microsoft Defender Trial |

---

## Prerequisites

- Global Administrator role
- Microsoft Defender Portal
- Microsoft Entra ID users

---

## Procedure

### Step 1

Login to Microsoft Defender Portal.

---

### Step 2

Navigate to

Settings

↓

Endpoints

↓

Permissions

↓

Roles

---

### Step 3

Click

Add Role

---

### Step 4

Configure

- Role Name
- Description

---

### Step 5

Select Permissions.

Example:

- View Alerts
- Manage Incidents
- Live Response
- Device Isolation

---

### Step 6

Assign users to the role.

---

### Step 7

Save the role.

---

## Verification

Verified that assigned users received only the configured permissions.

